00:19:25,001 --> 00:19:27,202
It's Hunsaker! Go! Go!

243
00:19:28,102 --> 00:19:30,503
I was just
messin' around with Chas.

244
00:19:30,603 --> 00:19:33,604
- Good evening, Charles.
- Hi, Mrs. Hunsaker.

245
00:19:39,706 --> 00:19:41,706
- What was that?
- I don't know, ma'am.

246
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:45,107
- Who were those boys?
What were they doing?
- Oh, who knows?

247
00:19:45,207 --> 00:19:47,208
- Charles?
- Um...

248
00:19:48,808 --> 00:19:52,609
- Did you make this scarf yourseIf?
- No, George, I bought it.

249
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:55,410
- 'Cause it's a beauty. It really is.
- Thank you, George.

250
00:19:55,510 --> 00:19:58,211
In case I don't see you before
the Thanksgiving holidays,

251
00:19:58,311 --> 00:20:01,212
- why don't you give me
one of your big hugs?
- Oh, George!

252
00:20:01,312 --> 00:20:03,213
- Please? Come on.
- Good evening, boys.

253
00:20:03,313 --> 00:20:05,513
Good-bye,
Mrs. Hunsaker.

254
00:20:24,919 --> 00:20:27,420
Mr. Trask is our fearless leader,

255
00:20:29,221 --> 00:20:32,022
a man of learning,
a voracious reader.

256
00:20:34,022 --> 00:20:37,223
He could recite the "lliad"
in ancient Greek...

257
00:20:38,023 --> 00:20:41,024
while fishing for trout
in a rippling creek.

258
00:20:42,425 --> 00:20:45,226
Endowed with wisdom,
of judgement sound,

259
00:20:47,226 --> 00:20:50,227
nevertheless about him
the questions abound.

260
00:20:55,529 --> 00:20:58,630
How does Mr. Trask
make such wonderful deals?

261
00:21:01,130 --> 00:21:04,131
Why did the trustees
buy him Jaguar wheels?

262
00:21:05,232 --> 00:21:07,232
He wasn't conniving!

263
00:21:07,532 --> 00:21:09,333
He wasn't crass!

264
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:13,234
He merely
puckered his lips...

265
00:21:15,435 --> 00:21:17,535
and kissed their ass!

266
00:21:35,441 --> 00:21:37,341
Come on.
Come on.

267
00:21:43,443 --> 00:21:45,844
One more!
One more, come on!

268
00:21:56,847 --> 00:21:58,148
Aah!

269
00:22:05,150 --> 00:22:06,750
Fuck you!

270
00:22:13,853 --> 00:22:15,853
Mr. Simms, Mr. Willis.

271
00:22:17,954 --> 00:22:19,154
Hmm.

272
00:22:20,455 --> 00:22:24,656
Mrs. Hunsaker says that you gentlemen
were at a vantage point last night...

273
00:22:24,756 --> 00:22:27,757
to observe who was
responsible for this, uh,

274
00:22:28,457 --> 00:22:29,758
stunt.

275
00:22:35,259 --> 00:22:36,860
Who was it?

276
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,861
I really couldn't
tell you, sir.

277
00:22:41,561 --> 00:22:44,962
Um, I thought I saw someone
fooling with the lamppost,

278
00:22:45,862 --> 00:22:49,063
but by the time I pulled focus,
they were gone.

279
00:22:50,364 --> 00:22:51,964
Mr. Simms?

280
00:22:54,265 --> 00:22:55,966
I couldn't say.

281
00:22:58,266 --> 00:23:01,467
That automobile is not
just a possession of mine.

282
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:05,969
That automobile was presented
to me by the Board of Trustees.

283
00:23:07,169 --> 00:23:11,570
It is a symbol of the standard
of excellence for which
this school is known,

284
00:23:12,471 --> 00:23:15,071
and I will not
have it tarnished.

285
00:23:15,572 --> 00:23:17,372
The automobile?

286
00:23:19,473 --> 00:23:21,673
The standard,
Mr. Willis.

287
00:23:25,174 --> 00:23:28,475
- What's your position, Mr. Simms?
- On what, sir?

288
00:23:29,476 --> 00:23:31,676
On preserving the
reputation of Baird.

289
00:23:31,776 --> 00:23:34,577
- I'm for Baird.
- Then, who did it?

290
00:23:37,278 --> 00:23:39,679
I really couldn't say for sure.

291
00:23:45,081 --> 00:23:46,681
Very well.

292
00:23:54,083 --> 00:23:56,484
First thing Monday,
I'm convening a special session...

293
00:23:56,584 --> 00:23:58,985
of the student-faculty
disciplinary committee.

294
00:23:59,085 --> 00:24:01,686
As this is a matter which
concerns the whole school,

295
00:24:01,786 --> 00:24:04,586
the entire student body
will be present.

296
00:24:04,787 --> 00:24:07,387
There will be no classes,
no activities.

297
00:24:07,487 --> 00:24:09,588
Nothing will transpire
at this institution...

298
00:24:09,688 --> 00:24:12,389
until that proceeding
is concluded.

299
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:18,591
And if, at that time,
we are no further along than we are now,

300
00:24:20,391 --> 00:24:22,492
I will expel you both.

301
00:24:27,694 --> 00:24:30,294
Mr. Willis,
would you excuse us?

302
00:24:33,895 --> 00:24:36,096
Have a nice Thanksgiving.

303
00:24:37,697 --> 00:24:39,697
Thank you.
You too, Mr. Willis.

304
00:24:39,797 --> 00:24:41,198
I will.

305
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:50,400
Mr. Simms.

306
00:24:51,201 --> 00:24:53,902
I'm not quite through
with you yet.

307
00:25:03,705 --> 00:25:06,705
One of the few perks
of this office is that...

308
00:25:07,206 --> 00:25:11,007
I am empowered to handle
certain matters on my own as I see fit.

309
00:25:12,607 --> 00:25:14,508
Do you understand?

310
00:25:14,608 --> 00:25:16,508
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

311
00:25:17,209 --> 00:25:20,310
The Dean of Admissions at Harvard
and I have an arrangement.

312
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:23,711
Along with the usual sheaf of applicants
submitted by Baird,

313
00:25:23,811 --> 00:25:25,711
of which virtually,

314
00:25:25,911 --> 00:25:28,812
oh, two-thirds are
guaranteed admittance,

315
00:25:29,612 --> 00:25:31,313
I add one name,

316
00:25:33,114 --> 00:25:36,415
somebody who's a standout
and yet, underprivileged;

317
00:25:37,115 --> 00:25:41,216
a student who cannot afford to pay
the board and tuition in Cambridge.

318
00:25:44,817 --> 00:25:48,318
Do you know on whose behalf
I drafted a memo this year?

319
00:25:48,618 --> 00:25:51,219
- No, sir.
- You. You, Mr. Simms.

320
00:25:57,321 --> 00:25:59,822
Now can you tell me
who did it?

321
00:26:02,122 --> 00:26:04,023
No, sir, I can't.

322
00:26:05,323 --> 00:26:08,624
You take the weekend
to think about it, Mr. Simms.

323
00:26:10,525 --> 00:26:12,226
Good afternoon.

324
00:26:15,026 --> 00:26:16,827
What'd he say?

325
00:26:17,427 --> 00:26:19,628
- Nothin'.
- What do you mean, nothing?

326
00:26:19,728 --> 00:26:22,029
He said the same thing.
He just said it over.

327
00:26:22,129 --> 00:26:24,129
You know what
he's doing?

328
00:26:24,229 --> 00:26:26,630
He's good-cop,
bad-coppin' us.

329
00:26:27,530 --> 00:26:29,731
He knows I'm old guard.
You're fringe.

330
00:26:29,831 --> 00:26:32,832
He's gonna bear down on me
and soft-soap you.

331
00:26:33,432 --> 00:26:36,133
Did he try to soft-soap you? Did he?

332
00:26:38,233 --> 00:26:39,434
No.

333
00:26:40,834 --> 00:26:43,935
Chas, I detect a slight panic pulse
from you. Are you panicking?

334
00:26:44,035 --> 00:26:46,336
- Yeah, a little.
- Come on.

335
00:26:46,536 --> 00:26:49,337
- You're on scholarship, right?
- Yeah.

336
00:26:49,937 --> 00:26:53,038
You're on scholarship
from Oregon... at Baird.

337
00:26:54,638 --> 00:26:57,139
You're a long way from home, Chas.

338
00:26:57,639 --> 00:26:59,940
What's that got to do
with anything?

339
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:02,341
I don't know how
it works out there.

340
00:27:02,441 --> 00:27:05,342
But how it works here?
We stick together.

341
00:27:06,042 --> 00:27:08,443
It's us against them,
no matter what.

342
00:27:08,543 --> 00:27:11,744
We don't cover our ass.
We don't tell our parents.

343
00:27:12,544 --> 00:27:14,545
Stonewall everybody!

344
00:27:15,345 --> 00:27:17,746
And above all,
never, never...

345
00:27:20,046 --> 00:27:22,747
Ieave any of us
twisting in the wind.

346
00:27:24,848 --> 00:27:26,548
And that's it.

347
00:27:26,848 --> 00:27:29,249
What does that have to do
with me being on scholarship?

348
00:27:29,349 --> 00:27:30,850
Hey, hey!

349
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:35,151
I'm just tryin' to bring you
up to speed, kid, that's it.

350
00:27:35,251 --> 00:27:36,651
Thanks.

351
00:27:39,652 --> 00:27:43,453
I'll tell you what. Give me a few hours
to figure out the moves,

352
00:27:43,954 --> 00:27:46,454
and call me tonight
in Vermont.

353
00:27:47,455 --> 00:27:50,456
I'll be at the Sugarbush lodge,
all right?

354
00:27:50,856 --> 00:27:52,356
All right.

355
00:27:53,556 --> 00:27:55,257
You all right?

356
00:27:56,057 --> 00:27:57,858
Yeah, I guess so.

357
00:27:59,058 --> 00:28:00,459
Okay.

358
00:28:03,059 --> 00:28:05,260
Try to keep him down
to four drinks a day.

359
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:08,261
If you can keep him down to forty,
you're doin' good.

360
00:28:08,361 --> 00:28:11,762
Try to water them down a little.
Do you know how to do that?

361
00:28:11,862 --> 00:28:15,963
- It's a long ride, honey!
- Get the bags in the car.
I'll be right out.

362
00:28:16,063 --> 00:28:19,164
Mommy, Mommy!
Don't forget Uncle Frank's walk.

363
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:22,665
Oh, ha... Yeah.

364
00:28:23,065 --> 00:28:25,466
Uh, you have to
air him out...

365
00:28:26,767 --> 00:28:28,767
a little every day.

366
00:28:29,167 --> 00:28:32,368
Why don't you go on back there,
get yourself oriented?

367
00:28:32,468 --> 00:28:36,270
I'll come out in a minute,
give you telephone numbers and stuff.

368
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:39,671
Well, I wouldn't try
a thing like that...

369
00:28:39,771 --> 00:28:41,871
unless I knew,
would I?

370
00:28:42,271 --> 00:28:44,172
Just let me
speak to her.

371
00:28:44,272 --> 00:28:46,173
Hello, beautiful.
Is that you?

372
00:28:46,273 --> 00:28:48,473
Yeah,
we spoke yesterday.

373
00:28:49,374 --> 00:28:52,174
You have a glass of wine
with lunch?

374
00:28:52,374 --> 00:28:54,775
You sound
a little dusky. Hmm.

375
00:28:55,976 --> 00:28:58,176
Just a minute, sweetheart.

376
00:28:59,977 --> 00:29:01,777
You're back, huh?

377
00:29:03,578 --> 00:29:05,078
Tenacious!

378
00:29:05,178 --> 00:29:08,579
Get out my dress blues.
They're in a garment bag in the closet.

379
00:29:08,679 --> 00:29:10,680
Check the top dresser drawer.
Take out the shoulder boards...

380
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:12,781
and affix them
shoulders right and left,

381
00:29:12,881 --> 00:29:15,081
A.S.A.P.
That means now.

382
00:29:15,582 --> 00:29:16,982
Hello.

383
00:29:17,582 --> 00:29:20,283
Sorry to keep you
waitin', sweetheart.

384
00:29:20,883 --> 00:29:23,384
I'm not the kind of guy
who likes to rush things,

385
00:29:23,484 --> 00:29:28,385
but I'm catchin' a 4:00
at Logan, lookin' out my window,
and there's not a taxi in sight.

386
00:29:29,286 --> 00:29:31,386
What happened to Chet?

387
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:33,687
He didn't invest
in a radio yet?

388
00:29:33,787 --> 00:29:36,388
Hah! Well,
get your driver on it.

389
00:29:37,088 --> 00:29:39,389
Tell him to get
a move on.

390
00:29:40,789 --> 00:29:42,290
Yes. Mmm.

391
00:29:43,690 --> 00:29:47,191
Some kind of body has got to go
with that bedroom voice.

392
00:29:47,991 --> 00:29:50,492
One day I'm gonna swing by,
get a better look at it.

393
00:29:50,592 --> 00:29:52,093
You bet.

394
00:29:53,293 --> 00:29:54,593
Bye.

395
00:29:58,295 --> 00:30:01,296
My val-pak's underneath the bed.
Get it out.

396
00:30:01,796 --> 00:30:03,896
Put the boards on the blues
and fold 'em in.

397
00:30:03,996 --> 00:30:06,697
Uh, are we going someplace,
Colonel?

398
00:30:07,597 --> 00:30:10,998
What business is that of yours?
Don't shrug, imbecile.

399
00:30:11,099 --> 00:30:14,299
I'm blind. Save your body language
for the bimbi.

400
00:30:16,100 --> 00:30:19,401
- Now, get my gear out.
- Francine, get in the car.

401
00:30:21,002 --> 00:30:24,703
It's almost 3:00. The goddamn
Flintstones haven't left yet.

402
00:30:25,403 --> 00:30:27,904
Willie Rossi must go in the car!

403
00:30:30,504 --> 00:30:33,405
- Here comes Mrs. Rossi now.
- Damn it!

404
00:30:34,306 --> 00:30:37,307
She said good-bye to me
three times today.

405
00:30:37,807 --> 00:30:39,907
What's she got,
separation anxiety?

406
00:30:40,007 --> 00:30:42,208
Cut her off
at the door!

407
00:30:44,409 --> 00:30:46,509
Hi, honey.
Bye, honey.

408
00:30:49,810 --> 00:30:52,211
I wish you were
coming with us.

409
00:30:52,311 --> 00:30:53,712
Me too.

410
00:30:54,612 --> 00:30:56,412
Maybe next time.

411
00:31:00,914 --> 00:31:03,314
- Drive carefully now.
- Yeah.

412
00:31:04,615 --> 00:31:07,116
Charlie, this is
where we'll be.

413
00:31:08,916 --> 00:31:12,117
Good luck, Charlie.
Don't let him drink too much.

414
00:31:15,818 --> 00:31:17,619
See ya, Charlie!

415
00:31:18,219 --> 00:31:21,220
And no 900 numbers.
He loves to talk dirty.

416
00:31:28,922 --> 00:31:31,323
All right,
let's get to work.

417
00:31:40,826 --> 00:31:43,227
L-buckles
givin' you trouble?

418
00:31:44,827 --> 00:31:47,028
Never in the Boy Scouts,
sluggo?

419
00:31:47,128 --> 00:31:50,229
- I made Tenderfoot.
- Tenderfoot, my foot!

420
00:31:50,829 --> 00:31:53,130
Convenience-store
mama's boy.

421
00:31:53,230 --> 00:31:55,330
Here. Let me
take a look at that.

422
00:31:55,430 --> 00:31:59,032
Touch me again, I'll kill ya,
you little son-of-a-bitch!

423
00:32:00,632 --> 00:32:02,833
I touch you.
Understand?

424
00:32:08,034 --> 00:32:11,835
My shoulder boards are in
the top dresser drawer. Get them, son.

425
00:32:12,136 --> 00:32:14,936
The epaulets with
the silver oak leaf.

426
00:32:32,542 --> 00:32:34,542
- Are these...
- Good.

427
00:32:35,543 --> 00:32:37,243
Taxi come yet?

428
00:32:38,043 --> 00:32:40,444
Colonel,
where are we going?

429
00:32:40,544 --> 00:32:42,345
Where we going?

430
00:32:42,545 --> 00:32:44,445
Freak show central.

431
00:32:45,046 --> 00:32:47,546
- Where's that?
- New York City.

432
00:32:49,747 --> 00:32:52,248
That's in New York, son.
New York State.

433
00:32:52,348 --> 00:32:56,149
Uh, Mrs. Rossi didn't say anything to me
about going anywhere.

434
00:32:56,749 --> 00:32:58,350
She forgot.

435
00:32:58,950 --> 00:33:02,051
- Should we call her, 'cause I...
- You kidding me?

436
00:33:02,151 --> 00:33:05,852
Call her? By the time they get to
Albany in that "hupmobile" he drives...

437
00:33:05,952 --> 00:33:08,553
it'll be opening day
at Saratoga.

438
00:33:08,753 --> 00:33:12,054
- Colonel, I can't go to New York City.
- Why not?

439
00:33:12,854 --> 00:33:14,455
New York...

440
00:33:14,955 --> 00:33:18,656
- New York's too much responsibility.
- Ah, responsibility!

441
00:33:18,756 --> 00:33:21,457
I had a lot of 17 year olds
my first platoon.

442
00:33:21,557 --> 00:33:23,957
I took care of them.
All set!

443
00:33:26,158 --> 00:33:27,859
How do I look?

444
00:33:28,859 --> 00:33:30,660
Tickets. Money.

445
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,160
Speech.

446
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:36,961
Old Washington joke...
from my days with Lyndon.

447
00:33:37,462 --> 00:33:40,262
I knew I could count on transportation.

448
00:33:41,463 --> 00:33:43,163
Are you ready?

449
00:33:45,464 --> 00:33:48,565
This is not Panmunjom.
A simple yes will do.

450
00:33:48,965 --> 00:33:50,966
- Um...
- Good! Here you go.

451
00:33:51,066 --> 00:33:53,366
Come on!
Hup to it, son!

452
00:33:54,067 --> 00:33:56,567
You're in front of me.
Let's go.

453
00:33:56,767 --> 00:33:58,868
Tomster, come here, boy.

454
00:34:00,269 --> 00:34:02,269
Psst, psst.
Come on.

455
00:34:02,969 --> 00:34:06,070
Here, tomster, come on.
Tomster, tomster. Yeah.

456
00:34:08,271 --> 00:34:10,772
Remember, when in doubt... fuck.

457
00:34:16,373 --> 00:34:18,874
Good afternoon, sir.
Where's our destination?

458
00:34:18,974 --> 00:34:21,875
Our destination... New York City,
home of the brave!

459
00:34:21,975 --> 00:34:25,076
- Two for the shuttle to New York.
- I'm not shuttling anywhere.

460
00:34:25,176 --> 00:34:28,977
- Look at those tickets. "First class".
- Yes, sir, first class.

461
00:34:29,077 --> 00:34:32,578
You bought me a ticket?
I never said I'd go to New York.

462
00:34:32,979 --> 00:34:37,080
What are you, some kind of chicken-shit,
sticks to job description only?

463
00:34:37,180 --> 00:34:38,880
Gate 46, sir.

464
00:34:39,180 --> 00:34:41,881
- As you were, son.
- Thank you, sir.

465
00:34:42,081 --> 00:34:44,082
Which way's the door?

466
00:34:44,682 --> 00:34:47,883
- Are you blind? Are you blind?
- Of course not.

467
00:34:48,883 --> 00:34:51,884
Then why do you keep grabbin'
my goddamn arm?

468
00:34:52,184 --> 00:34:53,985
I take your arm.

469
00:34:58,886 --> 00:35:00,887
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be sorry.

470
00:35:00,987 --> 00:35:04,088
How would you know,
watchin' MTV all your life?

471
00:35:04,188 --> 00:35:05,488
Yes!

472
00:35:07,989 --> 00:35:10,290
- Jack Daniels...
- You bet.

473
00:35:12,391 --> 00:35:15,191
and Diet Slice.
- The old Diet Slice.

474
00:35:15,692 --> 00:35:17,992
- And a water.
- Thank you, Daphne.

475
00:35:18,092 --> 00:35:19,793
Certainly, sir.

476
00:35:24,994 --> 00:35:26,595
Ahh! Mmm!

477
00:35:27,095 --> 00:35:29,396
How did you know her name?

478
00:35:30,996 --> 00:35:33,297
Well, she's
wearin' Floris.

479
00:35:34,397 --> 00:35:36,698
That's an
English cologne.

480
00:35:37,698 --> 00:35:40,399
But her voice is
California chickie.

481
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:45,201
Now, California chickie
bucking for English lady...

482
00:35:45,801 --> 00:35:47,701
I call her Daphne.

483
00:35:49,502 --> 00:35:53,103
Oh, big things may happen to
that little thing of yours.

484
00:35:55,504 --> 00:35:57,204
