01:24:00,085 --> 01:24:02,686
It's simple. That's what makes
the tango so great.

1207
01:24:02,786 --> 01:24:06,287
If you make a mistake,
get all tangled up, just tango on.

1208
01:24:07,688 --> 01:24:09,588
Why don't you try?

1209
01:24:14,990 --> 01:24:16,891
Will you try it?

1210
01:24:17,691 --> 01:24:20,092
All right.
I'll give it a try.

1211
01:24:21,292 --> 01:24:23,193
Hold me down, son.

1212
01:24:30,995 --> 01:24:32,495
Your arm.

1213
01:24:35,296 --> 01:24:36,697
Charlie,

1214
01:24:37,997 --> 01:24:40,498
I'm gonna need some
coordinates here, son.

1215
01:24:40,598 --> 01:24:42,899
The floor's
about 20 by 30,

1216
01:24:43,699 --> 01:24:45,999
and you're at
the long end.

1217
01:24:46,700 --> 01:24:50,201
There's tables on the outside.
The band's on the right.

1218
01:27:29,750 --> 01:27:32,550
Oh, Frank, you are
one incredible dancer.

1219
01:27:36,952 --> 01:27:39,352
Wait'll you see
Charlie dance.

1220
01:27:40,653 --> 01:27:43,854
- He's a liar. I don't dance.
- Isn't he a charmer, though?

1221
01:27:43,954 --> 01:27:47,955
Truth is, not only can he dance,
but he'll sing you a hell of a tune.

1222
01:27:48,155 --> 01:27:50,856
He can do bird calls
and imitate Bela Lugosi.

1223
01:27:50,956 --> 01:27:52,857
- Hi, honey.
- Hey.

1224
01:27:52,957 --> 01:27:55,958
Michael, this is Frank
and this is Charlie.

1225
01:27:56,758 --> 01:28:00,359
-Hi, Frank, Charlie. I'm sorry I'm late.
-Oh, that's okay.

1226
01:28:00,459 --> 01:28:03,060
These two gentlemen
entertained me,

1227
01:28:03,260 --> 01:28:04,960
and time flew.

1228
01:28:05,060 --> 01:28:07,961
Your girl is...
a hell of a tango dancer.

1229
01:28:08,962 --> 01:28:12,263
You found someone to tango with.
That's terrific!

1230
01:28:12,463 --> 01:28:14,463
Let me
shake your hand.

1231
01:28:14,563 --> 01:28:18,164
- No, it was Frank.
- Hell, I'll shake both your hands!

1232
01:28:19,365 --> 01:28:22,066
Honey, this looks like the place,
but we gotta go.

1233
01:28:22,166 --> 01:28:25,267
We got a date with Darryl
and Carol in the village.

1234
01:28:25,367 --> 01:28:27,267
Do you have a check?

1235
01:28:27,367 --> 01:28:30,768
- Michael, please. My pleasure.
- No, no. I got this.

1236
01:28:32,169 --> 01:28:34,969
Michael, get your hand outta
your pocket. I'll take it. Really.

1237
01:28:35,070 --> 01:28:36,570
Allow me.

1238
01:28:38,671 --> 01:28:40,471
Why, thank you.

1239
01:28:41,271 --> 01:28:42,772
Bye, guys.

1240
01:28:43,272 --> 01:28:44,572
Bye.

1241
01:28:52,675 --> 01:28:54,776
Darryl and Carol.
Yeah.

1242
01:29:04,378 --> 01:29:07,679
It's Apartment 17E, Colonel.
She's expecting you.

1243
01:29:07,880 --> 01:29:11,681
You don't have to worry about a thing.
She's the creme de la creme.

1244
01:29:11,781 --> 01:29:13,281
My buddy took the Vice Chancellor
of Germany to her.

1245
01:29:13,381 --> 01:29:15,782
Now he wants to immigrate
to this country.

1246
01:29:15,882 --> 01:29:17,883
You did good, hombre.

1247
01:29:20,283 --> 01:29:22,284
My hair,
how is it?

1248
01:29:23,184 --> 01:29:24,885
It's perfect.

1249
01:29:27,986 --> 01:29:31,787
- I got the red foulard okay, didn't I?
- Yeah, real dark red.

1250
01:29:32,287 --> 01:29:34,588
Burgundy, Charlie,
burgundy.

1251
01:29:34,788 --> 01:29:36,388
They love it.

1252
01:29:37,689 --> 01:29:39,189
Bay Rum.

1253
01:29:41,290 --> 01:29:42,890
Windsor knot.

1254
01:29:44,391 --> 01:29:46,791
That's my heart
I'm feelin'.

1255
01:29:57,095 --> 01:29:58,595
I'm off.

1256
01:30:16,200 --> 01:30:18,201
Can you get long distance
on this?

1257
01:30:18,301 --> 01:30:20,402
And how.
Be my guest.

1258
01:30:31,805 --> 01:30:34,606
- Sugarbush lodge.
- Hi. George Willis, please?

1259
01:30:34,706 --> 01:30:36,607
One moment, please.

1260
01:30:38,107 --> 01:30:40,108
- Hello?
- Ah, Harry?

1261
01:30:40,208 --> 01:30:42,108
Chas, how are you?

1262
01:30:42,508 --> 01:30:45,609
You just caught us. We're about
to shoot George over to the airport.

1263
01:30:45,709 --> 01:30:48,410
Why is George
going to the airport?

1264
01:30:48,610 --> 01:30:52,111
Um, hold on. Maybe you should talk
to the man himself.

1265
01:30:53,312 --> 01:30:55,312
- Chas.
- Yeah. Hi, George.

1266
01:30:55,412 --> 01:30:58,813
- You just caught me.
- Harry said. Where you goin'?

1267
01:30:59,514 --> 01:31:01,514
- Home.
- To Boston?

1268
01:31:02,014 --> 01:31:04,915
Catching the puddle jumper.
Keep your fingers crossed.

1269
01:31:05,015 --> 01:31:07,416
What are you
going home for?

1270
01:31:08,616 --> 01:31:11,517
I was thinking, Chas.
This asshole, Trask?

1271
01:31:12,418 --> 01:31:14,718
He's making
no sense at all.

1272
01:31:15,218 --> 01:31:18,720
Somebody's gotta talk to him.
My father's Class of '59.

1273
01:31:19,020 --> 01:31:22,821
Your father? I thought we were
gonna keep our parents outta this.

1274
01:31:22,921 --> 01:31:26,322
This guy Trask is outta control, Chas.
Outta control!

1275
01:31:27,222 --> 01:31:29,523
Somebody's gotta
talk to him.

1276
01:31:29,623 --> 01:31:33,324
- My father's a major
fund-raiser, you know.
- No, I didn't.

1277
01:31:33,624 --> 01:31:36,425
Just relax.
He'll get us off the hook.

1278
01:31:37,525 --> 01:31:40,526
- I gotta go. Everything all right?
- Sure.

1279
01:31:40,726 --> 01:31:43,527
- I'lI see you Monday. Good-bye.
- Bye.

1280
01:32:08,835 --> 01:32:11,336
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

1281
01:32:23,239 --> 01:32:24,940
Hiya, Charlie.

1282
01:32:26,740 --> 01:32:28,441
Watch the door.

1283
01:32:46,646 --> 01:32:48,747
What a beautiful woman.

1284
01:33:02,451 --> 01:33:05,252
- Hello, there.
- Do you see what I see?

1285
01:33:06,452 --> 01:33:09,153
Yeah.
Either there's something wrong,

1286
01:33:09,753 --> 01:33:12,154
or we got the
world's worst hangover.

1287
01:33:12,254 --> 01:33:14,155
Won't you come in?

1288
01:33:34,361 --> 01:33:35,861
Colonel?

1289
01:33:48,965 --> 01:33:51,066
Colonel,
you all right?

1290
01:33:52,266 --> 01:33:54,067
What is there?

1291
01:33:58,768 --> 01:34:01,969
It's afternoon.
You've been sleeping all morning.

1292
01:34:04,070 --> 01:34:05,571
So what?

1293
01:34:06,771 --> 01:34:09,072
I don't know.
I thought...

1294
01:34:14,773 --> 01:34:16,774
I-I talked to George
last night.

1295
01:34:16,874 --> 01:34:18,374
His, ah...

1296
01:34:19,175 --> 01:34:23,076
His father's a big-deal alumnus
at school. He's got a lot of pull.

1297
01:34:23,676 --> 01:34:25,076
Really?

1298
01:34:26,777 --> 01:34:28,578
Yeah, he's, ah,

1299
01:34:30,678 --> 01:34:32,879
he's gonna talk
to the headmaster.

1300
01:34:32,979 --> 01:34:36,280
George thinks he might
be able to get us off the hook.

1301
01:34:36,380 --> 01:34:38,381
"Get us off the hook".

1302
01:34:39,181 --> 01:34:41,782
Yeah, that's...
that's what he said.

1303
01:34:41,982 --> 01:34:43,882
Watch the "us" part.

1304
01:34:47,583 --> 01:34:50,884
Colonel, don't you wanna
get up and do something?

1305
01:34:54,686 --> 01:34:56,186
Colonel?

1306
01:34:56,586 --> 01:34:58,987
Oh, Charlie,
what do ya want?

1307
01:35:00,187 --> 01:35:01,888
I don't know!

1308
01:35:02,288 --> 01:35:04,689
But you're
making me nervous.

1309
01:35:08,390 --> 01:35:10,690
My wallet is on
the dresser.

1310
01:35:11,591 --> 01:35:13,791
Take out
your plane ticket...

1311
01:35:13,891 --> 01:35:16,192
and $400
mustering-out pay,

1312
01:35:18,793 --> 01:35:20,293
plus...

1313
01:35:21,294 --> 01:35:23,394
airport-to-school taxi.

1314
01:35:27,195 --> 01:35:29,996
Colonel, it's no rush.
I mean, I can...

1315
01:35:30,396 --> 01:35:32,297
I could stay
for a while.

1316
01:35:32,397 --> 01:35:34,998
Charlie, you already
gave me a day.

1317
01:35:36,398 --> 01:35:39,099
For that day,
I am eternally grateful.

1318
01:35:42,100 --> 01:35:44,701
But right now I have...
other plans.

1319
01:35:46,902 --> 01:35:49,302
What other plans
do you have?

1320
01:35:51,603 --> 01:35:53,203
To die, son.

1321
01:35:53,704 --> 01:35:55,604
Colonel, you're...

1322
01:35:57,905 --> 01:36:00,606
Come on, Colonel,
you're not gonna die today.

1323
01:36:00,706 --> 01:36:03,006
Charlie,
give me your hand.

1324
01:36:08,408 --> 01:36:10,509
You go now, boy.
Okay?

1325
01:36:12,809 --> 01:36:14,810
You go.
Just, uh...

1326
01:36:18,411 --> 01:36:20,712
Just leave me
sleep here.

1327
01:36:21,912 --> 01:36:24,713
Look, uh...
Can we start over, please?

1328
01:36:25,113 --> 01:36:28,014
What do you feel
like doin' today, huh?

1329
01:36:29,515 --> 01:36:31,915
I mean, look at this.
The sun is shining!

1330
01:36:32,015 --> 01:36:34,416
It's a beautiful day.
Let's...

1331
01:36:37,817 --> 01:36:41,018
Colonel, I know you don't want
to be a party poop,

1332
01:36:41,418 --> 01:36:45,119
so let's go out and do something, huh?
Let's go for a ride.

1333
01:36:50,621 --> 01:36:52,322
Yeah, a ride.

1334
01:36:52,922 --> 01:36:54,322
A ride?

1335
01:36:56,123 --> 01:36:58,924
Yeah, Colonel Slade,
what do you say?

1336
01:37:00,024 --> 01:37:02,225
Let's go for a ride,
huh?

1337
01:37:09,727 --> 01:37:11,727
What kind of ride?

1338
01:37:12,628 --> 01:37:15,329
Yeah, this is a valid
Oregon driver's license,

1339
01:37:15,429 --> 01:37:18,930
and we let appropriate customers
test-drive the Testarossa.

1340
01:37:19,030 --> 01:37:22,631
But you're 17 and with
a blind companion. That we don't do.

1341
01:37:23,031 --> 01:37:25,832
This is a $190,000
piece of machinery.

1342
01:37:26,032 --> 01:37:29,433
- I'm not letting it out this door.
- How 'bout this one over here?

1343
01:37:29,533 --> 01:37:32,134
That's a Cabriolet T.
The same deal.

1344
01:37:32,434 --> 01:37:36,735
Think I'm gonna let an unaccompanied kid
get behind the wheel of a $110,000 car?

1345
01:37:36,835 --> 01:37:39,236
He will not be
unaccompanied.

1346
01:37:39,436 --> 01:37:41,937
I'll be with him.
I'm his father.

1347
01:37:43,037 --> 01:37:45,438
- You're his father?
- Yes.

1348
01:37:46,138 --> 01:37:49,439
I have an idea. Why don't I take
your father for a test-drive?

1349
01:37:49,539 --> 01:37:53,440
- What's your quota, Freddie?
- Don't worry about my quota. I do well.

1350
01:37:53,540 --> 01:37:55,441
How many Ferraris
you sold this month?

1351
01:37:55,541 --> 01:37:58,242
That's not relevant
to this discussion.

1352
01:37:58,342 --> 01:38:00,442
Freddie,
the 80s are over.

1353
01:38:00,542 --> 01:38:03,243
Are you tryin' to tell me
these are just walkin' outta the store?

1354
01:38:03,343 --> 01:38:07,444
This is a Ferrari, the finest machinery
made in the automobile industry.

1355
01:38:07,544 --> 01:38:10,445
If you like it that much,
why are you sellin' it?

1356
01:38:10,545 --> 01:38:15,047
- I'd love to accommodate you...
- If this car performs
the way I expect it to,

1357
01:38:15,447 --> 01:38:19,848
you'll get a certified check of $101,000
and change when you come in tomorrow.

1358
01:38:20,949 --> 01:38:23,649
It's $109,000,
plus $950, plus tax.

1359
01:38:25,650 --> 01:38:27,551
Freddie, for you...

1360
01:38:28,651 --> 01:38:30,251
107 all in,

1361
01:38:30,952 --> 01:38:34,453
plus a case of champagne
to go with your leftover turkey.

1362
01:38:34,553 --> 01:38:37,554
What do you say?
Don't worry about the boy.

1363
01:38:38,554 --> 01:38:42,055
He drives so smooth,
you can boil an egg on the engine.

1364
01:38:42,255 --> 01:38:45,356
When we bring the car back,
I'll peel the egg for ya.

1365
01:38:45,456 --> 01:38:49,057
Listen, you made me laugh,
but I can't let the car go out.

1366
01:38:51,458 --> 01:38:53,258
Want a deposit?

1367
01:38:53,459 --> 01:38:56,159
This is not an
installment item, sir.

1368
01:38:59,660 --> 01:39:02,561
Freddie, you're no
spring chicken, are ya?

1369
01:39:05,362 --> 01:39:09,363
Well, you know what they call me
at the home office? The gray ghost.

1370
01:39:09,663 --> 01:39:11,964
You know why they
still keep me around?

1371
01:39:12,064 --> 01:39:15,465
There's no kid here that
can move a Ferrari like I can.

1372
01:39:15,565 --> 01:39:18,366
I'm known from coast to coast
like butter and toast.

1373
01:39:18,466 --> 01:39:20,667
Ask anybody about
Freddie Bisco.

1374
01:39:20,767 --> 01:39:23,568
When I get a Ferrari...
out the door!

1375
01:39:23,868 --> 01:39:26,669
- Hah! You just made me laugh.
- Yeah?

1376
01:39:27,569 --> 01:39:29,169
Two thousand.

1377
01:39:31,470 --> 01:39:34,571
Unless you take it,
you're gonna make me cry.

1378
01:39:37,672 --> 01:39:39,673
I'm a gray ghost too.

1379
01:39:50,976 --> 01:39:53,277
See? This is fun,
isn't it?

1380
01:40:07,081 --> 01:40:09,082
Drop her into neutral.

1381
01:40:10,582 --> 01:40:13,283
Slide her into second.
Pop the clutch.

1382
01:40:51,595 --> 01:40:54,596
Straight. Hold it
right like that. Feel it?

1383
01:40:55,496 --> 01:40:58,297
That's straight.
Just keep it straight.

1384
01:41:01,698 --> 01:41:04,699
- Keep it straight.
- No fun just to keep it straight.

1385
01:41:04,799 --> 01:41:07,900
You've got to move a little bit,
feel the road.

1386
01:41:08,100 --> 01:41:11,101
Please? Just like this.
All right? There you go.

1387
01:41:11,201 --> 01:41:13,301
Take it nice and easy.

1388
01:41:14,202 --> 01:41:16,102
Do you like this?

1389
01:41:19,303 --> 01:41:22,404
Slow it down a little.
You goin' a little fast.

1390
01:41:22,804 --> 01:41:24,805
Colonel, slow it down.

1391
01:41:26,305 --> 01:41:28,806
Something's happened
to my foot!

1392
01:41:30,206 --> 01:41:32,207
- Slow it down, please.
- Hold on, Charlie.

1393
01:41:32,307 --> 01:41:34,408
I think I've got
another gear.

1394
01:41:34,508 --> 01:41:36,208
Colonel Slade?

1395
01:41:38,409 --> 01:41:40,510
- Whoo-ah!
- Oh shit!

1396
01:41:40,810 --> 01:41:42,410
Watch out!

1397
01:41:43,611 --> 01:41:45,111
Hah-hah!

1398
01:41:45,611 --> 01:41:47,612
You'll get us killed!

1399
01:41:47,712 --> 01:41:50,513
Don't blame me, Charlie.
I can't see!

1400
01:41:52,013 --> 01:41:54,014
Colonel, slow it down!

1401
01:42:03,116 --> 01:42:05,117
Oh, God.
Oh, Jesus!

1402
01:42:06,017 --> 01:42:08,618
Now let's see
how this baby corners.

1403
01:42:08,818 --> 01:42:11,219
- Corners?
- Yeah. Say when.

1404
01:42:11,919 --> 01:42:14,520
- Say when what?
- Say when to turn.

1405
01:42:14,620 --> 01:42:18,121
- Colonel, you can't turn the car.
- Where's the turn, Charlie?

1406
01:42:18,221 --> 01:42:21,122
3:00? 2:00?
Right oblique? Right face?

1407
01:42:22,222 --> 01:42:23,923
Come on!
Talk to me!

1408
01:42:24,023 --> 01:42:26,224
Ah... it's left, I guess.

1409
01:42:26,524 --> 01:42:28,924
Left. I knew it.
Okay. Now?

1410
01:42:31,425 --> 01:42:33,726
No, no!
Not now! Not now!

1411
01:42:34,026 --> 01:42:36,327
- Now?
- Colonel, please?

1412
01:42:36,927 --> 01:42:41,128
Charlie, I'm gonna do it anyway.
Whether you say so or not, here we go!

1413
01:42:41,328 --> 01:42:43,829
Okay! Wait, wait, wait!
Just wait!

1414
01:42:43,929 --> 01:42:45,529
Here I go.

1415
01:42:46,230 --> 01:42:47,830
Wait... now!

1416
01:42:54,032 --> 01:42:56,233
I did it!
Oh, Charlie!

1417
01:42:58,934 --> 01:43:01,734
You're ridin' with
one very happy man!

1418
01:43:03,635 --> 01:43:06,236
- Turn again!
- Be specific, son.

1419
01:43:06,936 --> 01:43:09,037
- Left now!
- Okay.

1420
01:43:10,337 --> 01:43:12,238
- Ohh!
- Whoo-ah!

1421
01:43:13,238 --> 01:43:14,938
I love this!

1422
01:43:16,139 --> 01:43:19,040
I love it!
Shall we take it to the max?

1423
01:43:20,240 --> 01:43:21,841
Let me out.

1424
01:43:22,641 --> 01:43:24,741
Shit! The yellow flag.

1425
01:43:27,242 --> 01:43:29,343
I hadn't even
opened her up yet.

1426
01:43:29,443 --> 01:43:31,744
- Which way's the curb?
- Pull over. Slow down!

1427
01:43:31,844 --> 01:43:33,744
- Slow down, Colonel.
- All right, I'm doin' it.

1428
01:43:33,844 --> 01:43:37,445
- Pull over to the curb. Slow it down.
- Yep, yep. Got it.

1429
01:43:48,649 --> 01:43:52,050
- Oh, Christ.
- Ooh, I haven't had a ticket in years.

1430
01:43:55,351 --> 01:43:57,351
I'll do the talking.

1431
01:44:03,353 --> 01:44:05,554
License and registration.

1432
01:44:16,757 --> 01:44:19,558
What? Are you
test-driving this baby?

1433
01:44:19,658 --> 01:44:21,759
Don't she purr though?

1434
01:44:21,859 --> 01:44:23,860
At 70 miles an hour?

1435
01:44:24,260 --> 01:44:26,760
You should hear her
at 125. Hah!

1436
01:44:27,561 --> 01:44:29,561
Where's your license?

1437
01:44:30,662 --> 01:44:32,462
At the dealer's.

1438
01:44:32,862 --> 01:44:35,763
They give it back
when you return the car.

1439
01:44:36,263 --> 01:44:38,564
- You got I.D.?
- You bet.

1440
01:44:41,865 --> 01:44:43,365
Indeed.

1441
01:44:47,067 --> 01:44:48,867
Lt. Col. Slade.

1442
01:44:49,167 --> 01:44:50,968
And you, solider?

